for current_combo in all_user_combos:
  print(f"User Selects Following Dimensions | {current_combo}")
  #Step 1: Filter Table for Audience v. No Audience
  if 'audience' in current_combo: 
    current_combo.remove('audience')
    current_combo.append('grain_value')
    df = (data_model.filter(f.col('grain').isin('targeting')))
  else: 
    df = (data_model.filter(f.col('grain').isin('ALL')))
  
  #Step 2: If Activation Name in Combo, group by Hash - Else group by the Provided Combo
  drop_cols = []
  group_by_cols = current_combo
  if 'activation_name' in current_combo:
    group_by_cols.extend(['activation_id_hash_key'])
    drop_cols.extend(['activation_id_hash_key'])
  if 'grain_value' in current_combo: 
    group_by_cols.extend(['audience_id_hash_key'])
    drop_cols.extend(['audience_id_hash_key'])
  display(df
          .groupBy(*group_by_cols)
          .agg(f.round(f.avg('sales_test_total'), 0).alias('Avg Sales'),

               )
          .drop(*drop_cols)
          .sort(*current_combo)
          )
